    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="grc" resp="#JP">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/>Πίδοσσα Πάρωνος
                    <lb n="2"/>τοῦ Ἐπιάνακτος
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                    <app><note>Text of Gualtherus and Franz</note></app>
                    <app loc="1"><note>Kaibel: [..]πιδος Σα[ρ]α[πί]ωνος. The suggestion of a lacuna at the start of the line is entirely speculative on the part of Kaibel.</note></app>
                    <app loc="2"><note>Gualtherus marks a '.' between the two words, but whether this is intended to signify an interpunct or a missing character is unclear.</note></app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation">
                <p><!--translation(s) - add @xml:lang for 'en' or 'it' to div--></p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>The text appears to be on a relief, possibly funerary, of which Gualtherus provides a drawing. There is no record of autopsy after Gualtherus and it appears to be lost. Kaibel's attempt to suggest a comprehensible text ignores the presentation of Gualtherus; Kaibel's reference to Gualtherus fails to indicate that the text is in the addenda, p.100, not the main sequence.</p>
            </div>
